
TLS stands for *Transport Layer Security*

"
  TLS allows client/server applications to communicate
  over the Internet in a way that is designed to prevent eavesdropping,
  tampering, and message forgery.
" [ https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc8446[RFC-4886] ]

TLS is the successor of → development/security/cryptography/SSL[SSL] (→ development/security/cryptography/SSL-TSL)

Version 1.3 of TLS is specified in → development/web/RFC#rfc-8446[RFC 8446]. Version 1.2 is specified in RFC 5246.
